cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper proposes a method for obtaining cross-lingual embeddings using neural language models.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper uses bidirectional LSTMs and linear transformations to learn the embeddings.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper proposes an unsupervised method for learning cross-lingual embeddings.
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is a possible category as the paper uses neural networks to learn the embeddings.
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is a less likely category as the paper does not focus on visual data, but it is still possible as the paper uses neural networks for learning.
